&lt;li&gt;Provide legal guidance on data privacy, Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act, corporate practice of medicine, consumer protection, and related risks associated with product design and operations. Lead negotiation of customer-facing contractual provisions relating to data rights, AI and machine learning usage, product functionality, and operational restrictions, and advise on the development of terms of service, disclosures, disclaimers, and other legal protections designed to support business objectives and mitigate litigation and enforcement risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with&amp;nbsp; Security and Compliance to support responsible AI governance initiatives,&amp;nbsp; including review of customer-specific requirements, contractual commitments, transparency obligations, and escalation of legal issues that may require modifications to AI functionality, data use practices, or product operations.,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Clinical team on legal issues related to telehealth services, pharmacy review, and health information exchange data including contract interpretation, liability analysis, legal risk assessment, negotiation of health information exchange and related agreements, and drafting of state-specific consent language, disclosures, disclaimers, notices, and other user-facing legal documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on intellectual property strategy, including patent, trade secret, and open-source software matters related to Hello Heart’s technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor relevant industry trends, emerging case law, enforcement actions, and litigation developments , including those related to AI and machine learning in healthcare, Food and Drug Administration requirements, telehealth, Medicare, Medicare Advantage, Medicaid, digital health intellectual property, and data rights.&lt;/li&gt;
